<html><head><title>Servers Down Again ...Friday 16th</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>Servers Down Again ...Friday 16th</h3><p>Servers are down to fix an exploit.  I believe it is due to the use of spirit shrouds in flagged zones, but I don't know if that is the case.<br><br><br>From Kytherea at EQLive:<br><br>Due to an exploit all servers will be coming down at 4am PDT on Friday, September 16th for approximately 4 hours. Sorry Folks!  No I am not going to share what the exploit is... <br><br>Here is the patch message:<br><br>September 16th, 2005<br>_____________________<br><br>Welcome to EverQuest: Depths of Darkhollow!<br>-------------------------------------------<br><br>** Skills **<br><br>- Language skills can now be advanced pass skill level 32 again.<br><br><br>** Miscellaneous **<br><br>- Fixed a bug with monster mission shrouds and their abilities.<br>- Fixed a problem that allowed the boar mount to go into dungeons.<br>- Mounts will sink when in water as they should.<br>- Fixed an issue with the /who command when people are shrouded.<br><br>-- The EverQuest Team <br> </div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Friday, 16 September, 2005<br>Link: <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=11044">http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=11044</a><br>Printed On: Sat Dec 10 9:28:56 PST 2005<br>©2005 IGN Entertainment</font></span>